<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean FM Urges SADC to Double Efforts for Regional Prosperity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean Minister of Foreign
Affairs Stan Mudenge today urged Southern African Development
Community (SADC) countries to make double efforts for peace and
stability so as to achieve economic prosperity in the region.
</P>
<P>
Mudenge told a one-day meeting of the SADC organ on politics,
defense and security here that economic perosperity in the region
could only be achieved if the 12 nations in the grouping remained
united.
</P>
<P>
"The SADC organ's objectives are vital for the well-being of
our people, aiming to ensure the flourishing of peace, security
and stability in our region, (which are) conditions for economic
development among our countries and peoples," he said.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the SADC organ and adoption of a protocol on
peace, security and conflict resolution were part of the process
to deepen the bonds of brotherhood and enhance the sense of
togetherness in souther Africa, Mudenge noted.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, delegates from all SADC member countries
held discussions on the draft protocol.
</P>
<P>
They are also expected to deliberate on specific issues such
as the troubled Congo (Brazzaville), the Comoros and the fragile
peace process in Angola.
</P>
<P>
The SADC organ on politics, defense and security was launched
at a SADC summit held last year in Gaborone, Botswana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
