<HEADLINE> European Shares Down, London Sheds 2.5 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Stock markets in London and
Frankfurt both sustained Thursday's decline and suffered heavy
losses today, with London shedding 125.5 points at close, the
biggest one day drop since October 1992.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index of leading British shares lost more than 120
points as weak futures and Wall Street blues took it below the
4,900-level.
</P>
<P>
Almost 22 billion pounds (35.2 billion US dollars) was wiped
off the value of top shares in the biggest one-day fall since
October 1992 when Britain pulled out of the European exchange rate
mechanism.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts stressed that this was due to technical
factors and was not the start of a long-awaited correction.
</P>
<P>
German shares in Frankfurt closed sharply lower in response to
the weak dollar and fears of an interest rate hike at next week's
Bundesbank meeting.
</P>
<P>
The major DAX-30 index finished the session 78.57 points lower
at 4,152.86.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse was closed for Assumption Day holiday. The
CAC-40 index ended 2.20 points down at 2,921.84 Thursday, a drop
of 74.43 points on last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
