<HEADLINE> Tajik President Sacks Customs Committee Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov
today signed a decree dismissing Yakub Salimov from his post of
chairman of the customs committee, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported from Dushanbe, the Tajik capital.
</P>
<P>
Salimov was one of the organizers of the recent armed conflict
in the Tajik capital. The reason for the dismissal was not
specified in the decree, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ismoil Davlyatov, former nature protection minister
of Tajikistan, was appointed chairman of the customs committee.
</P>
<P>
It was said that Salimov started mobilizing his supporters,
since the situation in the southeast of Dushanbe is tending
towards tension.
</P>
<P>
In the area of the Vakhsh, 20 kilometers to the south of the
city of Kurgan-Tyube, there are up to 500 armed militants loyal to
Salimov who is prepared to back the rapid reaction brigade
commander Mahmud Khudoiberdiyev.
</P>
<P>
Khudoiberdiyev was relieved by the Tajik president from his
post of commander of a presidential rapid reaction brigade
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to another report from Kurgan-Tyube, talks between
Deputy Commander of collective peacekeeping forces in Tajikistan
Major-General Pavel Lipskyand and Colonel Makhmud Khudoiberdyev
ended to no avail today after being held for five minutes only.
</P>
<P>
Khudoiberdyev had arrived at the request of the Tajik president
who asked him to render assistance to the state commission in
charge of surrender and handover of weapons and property of the
rapid deployment force brigade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
