<HEADLINE> Annan Recommends Sizeable UN Presence in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today recommended further postponement of the
withdrawal of the U.N. military units from Angola and retainment
in the country of up to 2,650 military personnel until the end of
October 1997.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Security Council, Annan said, "The peace
process in Angola was experiencing some of the most serious
difficulties since the signing of the Lusaka Protocol. The
progress achieved during the previous two and a half years is
being severely undermined by persisting tensions throughout the
country. Everything possible should be done to reverse this
ominous trend."
</P>
<P>
"Both parties bear a heavy responsibility for the future of the
peace process and must refrain from any action that leads to
renewed fighting. It is obvious that the current state of affairs
is mainly the result of delays by the National Union for the Total
independence of Angola (UNITA) in implementing its obligations
under the Lusaka Protocol," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
"The complete demilitarization of UNITA, the restoration of
state administration throughout the country, the transformation of
radio VORGAN into a non-partisan station and the true
transformation of UNITA into a political party are imperatives for
the implementation of the peace process," Annan stressed.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief said the Security Council would continue to
exercise its authority and take all necessary steps to ensure full
compliance with its decisions and last-minute half-hearted
concessions by UNITA, under pressure and on the eve of Security
Council deliberations were no longer acceptable.
</P>
<P>
Annan urged the parties, in particular UNITA, to respect the
safety and the security of personnel of the United Nations, its
programs and agencies, as well as the staff of other international
organizations who had been helping the Angolan people to achieve a
long-awaited peace, national reconciliation and economic
rehabilitation of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
