tourists survived of the Friday ship capsize at Manila Bay
returned back tonight.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the seven Hong Kong residents drowned in the
accident were also carried to Hong Kong in the same plane.
</P>
<P>
Upon Arriving in Manila on Friday morning, the group of the
Hong Kong tourists went sightseeing at Manila Bay before their
boat capsized under strong winds and huge waves. All the Hong
Kong tourists and a local guide abroad fell into the sea.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine navy immediately dispatched vessels to their
rescue. Seven of the Hong Kong residents lost their lives in the
mishap.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Embassy in Manila sent officials to the accident
scene, the hospital and the headquarters of the Philippine Navy.
The Chinese officials conveyed regards to the victims and bought
clothes and food to them.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), has sent his condolences to families
of the victims who died Friday in a boat accident in the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Tung said he was saddened to learn of the boat
incident involving a number of Hong Kong residents in the
Philippines.
