<HEADLINE> Olympic Titlist Bellutti Takes Pursuit Gold at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Antonella Bellutti, Italian
Olympic champion won the women's 3,000-meter individual pursuit
event Saturday in the World Cup in Adelaide, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Bellutti, who arrived Friday after a long trip from her
high-altitude training camp in Bolivia, clocked 3 minutes 38.51
seconds in her final, beating American Karen Kurrek by nearly
eight seconds.
</P>
<P>
Bellutti's time set a new track record, saving about five
seconds off the mark set last September by Australian Lucy
Tyler-Sharman, who will be one of Bellutti's main rivals in the
event at the world championships in Perth later this month.
</P>
<P>
South African Jean-Pierre Van Zyl beat Latvian Ainars Kiksis
2-0 in the ride-off for the men's sprint gold, while Canadian
Tanya Dubnicoff downed compatriot Lori-Ann Muenzer 2-0 in their
women's sprint final.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Olympics bronze medallist Stuart O'Grady of Australia
won the men's 30-kilometer points race with 34 points from
Denmark's Jakob Piil on 32. Glen Thomson of New Zealand took the
bronze on 31.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand won the men's teams pursuit gold in 4:12.73,
beating the United States to second.  
</P>
