<HEADLINE> Tianjin Signed Economic Cooperation Agreements with Gansu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The industrial city of Tianjin
in north China signed 19 aid-the-poor and economic co-operation
agreements with Gansu province in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by Gansu officials and Zhang
Lichang, the mayor of Tianjin, who had headed a Tianjin
delegation to the under-developed province.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreements, 14 Tianjin districts and counties
will help 13 of Gansu's counties provide food and clothing for
farmers, build 11 primary schools for poor children, train 500
people in various fields, and send Tianjin education, medical, and
scientific personnel to Gansu to give lectures.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that Tianjin and Gansu will increase industrial,
trade, scientific and commercial co-operation and establish sales
centers and hold trade fairs.
</P>
<P>
The State Council decided in May of 1996 to let Tianjin help
Gansu with economic development and the two have started 122
aid-the-poor and economic co-operation projects.  
