<HEADLINE> Rapid Growth In Mobile Phone Use In South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China's island province of Hainan
has seen rapid growth in the number of mobile phones users, which
reached 100,000 by the end of July.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, when Hainan got its first mobile phone, the
province's analogue mobile telephone communications network has
developed to where it connects with all other parts of the country
except the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Regions and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The province's digital mobile phone network is connected to
China's 261 cities and prefectures in 29 provinces, municipalities
and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Hainan also started an international roaming service with Hong
Kong and Singapore, and will open the service with Macao, Finland,
Germany and other countries.
</P>
<P>
The mobile phone coverage rate in Haikou, the provincial
capital, has reached 12 percent, ranking first among China's
provincial capitals. Haikou's total telephone coverage rate is now
40 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
