<HEADLINE> Panda Dies in Central China Zoo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Shunshun, a female giant
panda, died of skin cancer in a zoo in Zhengzhou, the capital of
Henan Province on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old animal was the only panda raised in central
China's Henan province and was the pet of all the city's citizens.
</P>
<P>
Last year, doctors found a tumour on her back and performed
surgery to remove it, but the cancer later spread. Doctors tried
various methods to save her life but ultimately failed.
</P>
<P>
Several days before Shunshun's death, a few primary school
students came to offer comfort to the animal.
</P>
<P>
A panda's life expectancy is about 30 years, so Shunshun could
be said to be in middle age.  
</P>
