<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-16 12:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Halt Funding Missile Program Worrying Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli authorities have
expressed their concern over a U.S. Congressional proposal to
halt funding for Israel's development of a ballistic missile
interceptor.
</P>
<P>
According to a report in the pro-government newspaper The
Jerusalem Post, unnamed Israeli defense sources expressed worry
and lobbyists in Washington are hoping to convince a joint
House-Senate conference committee to overturn the proposal.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. House Appropriations Committee recently recommended
that funding for the Israeli-U.S. Boost Phase Intercept (BPI)
program be diverted to a far more ambitious U.S. Air Force program
called Air Borne Laser. BPI is a major component of Israel's
emerging anti-missile defense system.
</P>
<P>
"We were hoping that we would have enough money to start some
of the development," a source said. " Now, all we could do is
feasibility (study), if the Senate proposal is accepted."
</P>
<P>
The feasibility study is being done by the Israel Aircraft
Industries and Rafael Israel Armament Development Authority.
</P>
<P>
The BPI program has been funded to the tune of 20 million
U.S. dollars over the last two years. Earlier this year, it was
agreed that the Clinton Administration would ask Congress for 34
million dollars, enough to complete the feasibility study and
begin work on a prototype.
</P>
<P>
BPI is a concept whereby unnamed air vehicles fly over enemy
territory and search for ballistic missile batteries. When a
missile is fired, a small high-velocity rocket is sent to destroy
the enemy projectile during the initial boost phase of launch.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Air Force wants funding for a program in which a
Boeing 747 spots the enemy missile launch and fires a
high-powered laser to destroy it. U.S. officials said that the
program is still in the pre-feasibility stage and that it will
take up to 2006 until production begins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970816.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
