<HEADLINE> Two Palestinians Given Life Sentence for Murdering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 16 (Xinhua) -- In a speedy trial, the
Palestinian court in Jericho today sentenced two Palestinians to
life imprisonment for murdering an Israeli taxi driver Friday.
</P>
<P>
Another 17-year-old Palestinian was sentenced to 15 years in
jail for his part in the murder. The three confessed killing the
taxi driver, 45-year-old Ben Baruch from Jerusalem, in an attempt
to steal his money and his white Mercedes-Benz car.
</P>
<P>
Today's trial came only hours after Baruch's body was found in
a well near Jericho according to the confession of the murders.
</P>
<P>
Israeli and Palestinian police cooperated in the search for
Baruch after he disappeared Thursday on his way to Jericho with a
passenger. Baruch's car was late found abandoned in a refugee camp
south of Jericho, which led the arrest the suspects by Palestinian
police.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian police immediately notified their Israeli
counterparts, who recovered Baruch's body from where it was hidden.
</P>
<P>
Israel praised the cooperation of the Palestinian police in
the rapid conclusion of the murder case.
</P>
<P>
Public Security Minister Avigdor Kahalani confirmed the full
cooperation from the Palestinian police, but he noted that the
joint efforts in fighting car theft were much easier than in the
fight against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Kahalani expressed the wish that cooperation between Israeli
and Palestinian security forces would continue in all levels to
the benefit of both sides.
</P>
<P>
Despite both sides agreed to resume full security cooperation
in fighting terrorism as a result of the mediation by U.S. peace
envoy Dennis Ross in the past week, Israel said it is still
waiting to see concrete steps taken by the other side to fight
extremist Islamic organizations and their infrastructure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
