<HEADLINE> Flame to Ignite National Games Torches Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- A flame to ignite torches for
the upcoming Eight Chinese National Games arrived here on
Saturday, just hours after being lit in Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
The fire, kept in a specially-made box, was burned out of the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center, where the handover
ceremony of the Hong Kong's return to China was held in midnight
of last June 30.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, and Wei Jizhong, vice chairman of the
Eighth National Games Organizing Committee, attended the
fire-burning ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"The rain paused when we lit the fire, but it had been raining
before the ceremony and kept raining after. We are really in good
luck, " said vice president of Shanghai Physical Culture and
Sports Commission Li Yuyi, who accompanied the fire back to
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
This was the first of two fires used to light torches for the
Eight Naitonal Games, which is scheduled to open in Shanghai on
October 12.
</P>
<P>
The other flame will be lit in Shanghai on August 23 at the
site of the first congress of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC),
which was held in 1921 and announced the founding of CPC.
</P>
<P>
Torches will be burned with the two fires by a Chinese leader
in a spectacular ceremony in Tiananmen Square and be relayed
across China. 
</P>
