<HEADLINE> 26 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-six militants of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed after being
tracked down by the Turkish security forces, an official statement
said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said the rebels, who escaped after assailed an army
position, were chased and finally gunned down by security forces
in a large-scale operation in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The group of PKK militants launched attacks late Wednesday
night on a position of the security forces near the
Turkish-Iranian border, killing one soldier and three village
guards and wounded three others, it said.
</P>
<P>
The security forces are continuing their military operation in
fighting against the PKK guerrillas in the region, it added.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist struggle
since August 1984 for autonomy in eastern and southeastern
Turkey. The protracted and bloody warfare has so far claimed over
27,000 lives. 
</P>
