<HEADLINE> 10 Italian Abducted Tourists Set Free in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- All the 10 Italian tourists
kidnaped by armed tribesmen Thursday in Yemen have been set free,
according to Yemeni security sources.
</P>
<P>
The four Italian tourists who were kidnaped Thursday in the
city of Amran, 45 kilometers north of Sanaa were released Friday,
a security source said here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
He said that the other six Italian tourists who were abducted
Thursday in Abyan province, 490 kilometers south of Sanaa, were
also freed Friday.
</P>
<P>
The kidnapers aim to malign Yemen's relations with some
friendly nations that have strong economic ties with the country,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They noted that such shameful acts are internationally
incriminated and will not affect the stable ties between Yemen
and other countries.
</P>
<P>
No details were available about the kidnapers' identities or
whether the two abductions were linked.
</P>
<P>
Tribesmen in Yemen sometimes kidnap foreigners to press for
money or government funds for projects, and the hostages are
later freed unharmed. 
</P>
