<HEADLINE> China Sets up Fund to Aid Poor University Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China today set up a fund that
will provide financial support for poor university students, as a
part of a national program in this respect.
</P>
<P>
The "Cross-Century Development Fund for Chinese University
Student", with a donation of 10 million yuan (some 1.2 million US
dollars) from a company in east China's Fujian Province, will help
poor students complete their study on campuses.
</P>
<P>
The idea of raising money for poor students was produced by the
Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Youth League and the
All-China Students Federation early last year.
</P>
<P>
Survey shows that some 10 percent of the students in a few key
Beijing-based universities find it difficult to pay tuition
fees. Many of the students come from families of farmers and urban
laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 poor students have received financial support
since last year, according to the students federation.  
