<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Kenyan newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Kenyan government is willing and ready to resume "tough
negotiations" with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) over the
lapsed key loan program, Central Bank of Kenya Governor Micah
Cheserem said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
-- The death toll due to the killing by unidentified gunmen on
Wednesday and Thursday in Likoni area of Mombasa, the Indian
Ocean port in Kenya, rose to 20 after security forces recovered
seven more bodies.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation
</P>
<P>
-- Battles between warring factions in Congo's capital
Brazzaville have intensified and spread to the north of the
country while the government accused rival militiamen of hiring
foreign mercenaries, state radio reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
-- Despite the threat of economic sanctions, Angola's former
rebels failed to respond adequately to U.N. orders to fully and
accurately disclose their military strength, international
mediators say. 
</P>
