<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes New History Book </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China has published a new
history book, the most complete one of its kind, to record major
events over the past 1.7 million years.
</P>
<P>
The 15-million-character book covers the history from the Stone
Age to February of 1997 when Deng Xiaoping passed away. It also
touches important events concerning the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
"The Complete Collection of National Affairs" is said to be the
first chronicle written in modern Chinese to follow the style of
Zizhi Tongjian, a famous ancient history book that provided
references for the ruling classes.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 historians have taken part in the compilation of the
huge book. It was published by the Tuanjie (Unity) Publishing
House. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
