<HEADLINE> Men with Fake Banknotes Caught in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Two Dar es Salaam
residents were brought to a local court on Friday charged with
being in possession of 996 fake 10,000-Shilling banknotes,
according to the local press today.
</P>
<P>
Prosecuting Assistant Inspector of Police, Jasan Mtinya told
the court that the accused, Antipas Shao (38) and Salome Lesi
(41), were found in possession of the said banknotes on August
12.
</P>
<P>
He said that 982 of the fake 10,000-Shilling banknotes were
marked with the same number AM 828455 while the other 14 notes
also had a common number AM 424468. The official exchange rate is
that 600 Shillings are equal to one US Dollar.
</P>
<P>
The court will make its judgement later this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
