<HEADLINE> 7th Hong Kong Tourist found dead in Boat Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Rescuers today found the body of
the 7th Hong Kong victim in Manila Bay, where a pleasure boat
carrying mostly Hong Kong tourists capsized Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The seventh victim was a little boy, who was with his parents
on a tour to the Philippines. Earlier, he was reported missing.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said so far there were only three Filipino crew
members still missing.
</P>
<P>
The mishap happened at 4:30 p.m. (local time) Friday when a
ferry boat carrying 49 people capsized by strong winds and high
waves some 300 meters away from the sea wall of the bay. It was
the second boat disaster of the day in the Philippines. Earlier,
an inter-island vessel sank in the Samar Sea off the central
island of Biliran. Twelve people, including a baby girl, drowned
and 16 were still missing.
</P>
<P>
The rescue operation was still undergoing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
