<HEADLINE> Ferreira Books Semi Spot in RCA Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Wayne Ferreira beat Magnus
Larsson in a tense tiebreaker for a 3-6, 6-3, 7-6 (12/10) victory,
sailing into the semifinals of the one-million-dollar RCA
Championships in Indianapolis Friday night.
</P>
<P>
The South African, winner in 1994, completed the competition in
one hour and 58 minutes, and will play sixth seed Carlos Moya of
Spain on Saturday on the way to his first title of the year.
</P>
<P>
Swedish Larsson led 5-2 in the decider, but Ferreira pulled
back to stretch the contest out even tighter as he scored the
victory.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Moya was relatively untroubled by Czech Jiri
Novak in his 6-3, 7-5 victory in one hour and 12 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The second semifinal will be contested by unseeded Australian
Mark Woodforde and No. 9 Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde outmaneuvered Andre Agassi 6-3, 5-7, 6-3, stopping
the American's comeback winning streak at three matches.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman needed more than two hours for a 5-7, 6-4, 7-5 defeat
of American Tommy Ho. 
</P>
</TEXT>
