<HEADLINE> Leprosy May be Treated at Home in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 16 (Xinhua) -- There is now cure for
Leprosy which can be administered to patients at home. Therefore
victims of the disease no longer need to be confined to special
centers.
</P>
<P>
This was said by Tanzanian Deputy Minister for Education and
Culture Gladness Mziray at the National Assembly in Dodoma on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mziray said that the dose to cure leprosy is administered for
between six months and two years.
</P>
<P>
She said that even leprosy victims who have become disabled
can be cured within their community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
