<HEADLINE> Seles Reaches Toronto Open Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Monica Seles of the
United States nipped qualifier Rita Grande of Italy 6-0, 6-0
Friday to reach the semifinals of the 926,250 US dollars Toronto
Open.
</P>
<P>
Against the 69th-ranked Grande, Seles boasted of a clean record
of winning all the games in the 42-minute competition.
</P>
<P>
"I hit some great shots that even surprised myself," said the
third-ranked Seles who will play seventh-seeded Conchita Martinez
of Spain in the semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Martinez recorded her sixth consecutive win over fourth-seeded
Lindsay Davenport of the United States by 6-4, 4-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The other semifinal will match fifth-seeded Anke Huber of
Germany and 10th-seeded American Mary Joe Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
Huber edged third-seeded Amanda Coetzer of South Africa 2-6,
6-1, 6-4 while Fernandez sailed further with a victory of 6-2, 6-7
(3-7), 6-4 over unseeded Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Seles had played Martinez 12 times, winning the first 11 in
straight sets, with Martinez breaking the ice with a 7-6, 6-4
victory in California three weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
