<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka To Develop Teacher Education System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government is to
develop its teacher education system by year 2000 under a 70
million U.S. dollar assistance program from the World Bank and the
Asian Development Bank, sources in the Education Ministry said
today.
</P>
<P>
Three new teacher training colleges will be established in the
Galle, Ratnapura and Bingiriya districts in addition to the
existing eleven colleges. Construction of the new colleges is
scheduled to commence in November this year, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
By year 2000 the intake of trainees to the training colleges in
the country will be doubled.
</P>
<P>
Plans are also underway to set up 84 training centers to
re-train all teachers in government schools so as to develop their
knowledge, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
