<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombo Port's Performance Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's port Authority today
said it has improved the Colombo Port's performance by handling
one million containers by August 15, equivalent to the total
containers for the whole of 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to port authority sources, the one-million-container
mark was reached by late October in 1996 while the total number
stood at 1,001,526 containers by August 15 this year.
</P>
<P>
The sources said this feat had been possible due to increased
economic activities in the country as well as the services newly
provided for ships carrying larger volumes in the Colombo Port.
</P>
<P>
Colombo Port handled 1.3 million containers in 1996, an
increase of 29 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
the port's financial performance has also been improved in the
past few years. Revenue in 1996 rose to 155.2 million U.S. dollars
from 117 million U.S. dollars in 1995 while pre-tax profits rose
to 41.4 million U.S. dollars from 22.1 million U.S. dollars in
1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
