<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to Elect Vice President Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- India today is scheduled to
elect its vice-president.
</P>
<P>
The president was elected on July 14 and he assumed office on
July 25.
</P>
<P>
Two candidates are in the fray for the vice-presidential
office. One is Andhra Pradesh Governor Krishan Kant while another
is Akali Dal leader Surjit Singh Barnala. Krishan Kant is expected
to win as he enjoys the combined support of the ruling United
Front and the Congress.
</P>
<P>
The electoral college of the vice-president comprises of 790
members of the Lok Sabha (lower house of parliament) and the Rajya
Sabha (upper house of parliament). the strength comes down to 779
with 11 vacancies in the upper house at the moment.
</P>
<P>
The office of the vice-president has fallen vacant after the
election of K.R. Narayanan as the new president of India last
month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
