<HEADLINE> Hungary, Slovakia to Improve Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian Prime Minister Horn
Gyula met with his Slovak counterpart Vladimir Meciar in a bid to
boost their bilateral relations, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Meciar arrived in Gyor, a city northwest to Budapest, earlier
today for a one-day unofficial visit aimed at patching up the
frayed ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both sides exchanged views on improving bilateral relations,
but the meeting produced no obvious results.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, relations between Hungary and Slovakia have
become tense over issues of minority groups, the hydropower
station on the Danube River and the execution of the
Hungarian-Slovak fundamental agreements. 
