<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bear Kills Two Campers in B.C. Park, Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A woman and a man were killed
by a black bear in a remote northern park in Canada's British
Columbia (B.C.) province, a report said today.
</P>
<P>
The woman's 13-year-old son and a man were also attacked and
suffered injuries.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred Thursday night as the four campers stumbled
through the brush between two hot springs in Liard River Hotsprings
Provincial Park.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses threw rocks and sticks at the aggressive bear, but
could not stop it from mauling the four people.
</P>
<P>
The black bear was shot and killed by a tourist who rushed to
get a gun, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The park was evacuated soon after the incident. It will remain
closed while an investigation is going on there.
</P>
<P>
It was the first fatal bear attack in the province this year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, six people were injured and one person was killed by
bear. In 1995, there were 11 injuries and two deaths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
