<HEADLINE> Canada Sees Budget Surplus in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian government recorded a
budget surplus of 1.08 billion U.S. dollars in June, the Finance
Department said today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that Canada's federal government has posted
consecutive monthly budgetary surpluses since the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
The latest monthly surplus was due to lower spending and rising
revenues from taxes, the government said.
</P>
<P>
In May, the budget surplus was 980 million dollars, compared
with a deficit of 420 million dollars a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Over the first three months of the current fiscal year, the
deficit was reported at 360 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Paul Martin has projected a budget deficit of
12.24 billion dollars for this fiscal year. 
</P>
