<HEADLINE> Brunei to Buy Three More Indonesian CN-235 Planes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Brunei has agreed to buy three
more Indonesian-made CN-235 planes, bringing its ordered number of
the aircraft to eight, an official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached here Friday during a meeting between
Brunei Armed Forces Commander Dato Paduka Seri Haji Husin Ahmad
and Indonesian State Minister for Research and Technology Bj.
Habibie, Indonesia's Nusantara Aircraft Industry (IPTN) Deputy
Director Heru Santoso said.
</P>
