<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, China to Enhance Long-Term Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 15 (Xinhua)-- The Czech Republic attaches great
importance to a comprehensive and long-term cooperation with China
on a higher level, Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Klaus made the remarks in meeting with visiting Chinese
Minister of Power Industry Shi Dazhen.
</P>
<P>
Klause said the Czech Republic is watching closely the rapid
growth of China and that his government is holding a positive
attitude toward the development of the Sino-Czech relations.
</P>
<P>
His country will not only develop its ties with European
countries, but also boost long-term and comprehensive cooperation
with other countries including China, Klause said.
