<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices Jump 8 percent in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Fuel prices in
Colombia will increase eight percent, the country's Mines Ministry
announced today.
</P>
<P>
Starting today, gasoline will cost 1,175 pesos (almost 1.1
U.S. dollars) a gallon, gasoline extra 1,600 pesos, and diesel
1,175, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
This is the second fuel price hikes since February 24 this
year when fuel prices rose 14 percent.
</P>
<P>
The increase in sales revenue will help offset costs of
operation of the Colombian state oil company Ecopetrol, which have
risen more than 20 percent because of damage to oil infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The damage was caused by the country's anti-government
guerrilla warfare.
</P>
<P>
The price of gasoline has increased 22 percent so far this
year, four percent above the inflationary target proposed by the
Bank of the Republic. 
