<HEADLINE> Stopping Illegal Charges For Overseas Investors In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has removed 60 forms used for illegal charges on
local foreign-funded enterprises, to help get more overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
According to the Guangxi government, 15 illegal charges imposed
on foreign-funded enterprises by local departments have been
stopped, and the use of 45 forms by other departments like public
security, land administration, and industrial and commercial
administration have been stopped.
</P>
<P>
Local government also made it illegal for any government
department to impose illegal levies of any kind on foreign-funded
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The province has taken steps in recent years to improve the
investment environment and has built many infrastructure projects
for energy, transportation and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
"This move will help reshape the image of Guangxi in the eyes
of foreign investors," local officials say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
