<HEADLINE> 6 Hong Kong Tourists Drown in Manila Bay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Six Hong Kong tourists have lost
their lives after a ferry boat they were aboard capsized by strong
winds and high waves Friday afternoon in Manila Bay, investigators
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The investigators said there were still one Hong Kong tourist
and three Filipino crew members missing.
</P>
<P>
Forty five tourists, mostly Hong Kong residents, and four crew
members were aboard the ship when the mishap happened at 4:30
p.m., some 300 meters away from the seawall of the bay.
</P>
<P>
A helicopter from the Philippine Navy was still hovering above
the scene this morning, searching for the missing ones.
</P>
<P>
After the accident occurred, the Chinese Embassy in Manila
immediately sent officials to the scene and the hospital to convey
regards to the victims and bought clothes and food to them.
