<HEADLINE> New Housing For 600,000 Beijing Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- There has been some progress in
building residential housing and renovating rundown houses in
Beijing's "Comfortable Housing" Project in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Some 600,000 Beijing residents have moved into new housing in
the past five years, according to the Municipal Urban and Rural
Construction Committee. This meant an additional 33 million
sq.m. of housing, raising per capita floor space from 8.31 sq.m. in
1992 to 9.33 sq.m. last year.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, work on about two
million sq.m. began and a fourth of that has been completed.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, about 2.9 million sq.m. of old housing has been
torn down and 4.9 million sq.m. renovated.
</P>
<P>
The "Comfortable Housing" Project, which was intended to help
families living in cramped quarters get more space, has provided
1.88 million sq.m. of housing for 21,000 such families.
</P>
<P>
With its help, about 10,000 families with per capita floor
space of less than four sq.m. will move into new housing by the
end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
