<HEADLINE> Agassi Ousted in RCA Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Andre Agassi was beaten by
Mark Woodforde in the quarterfinals of the one-million US dollars
RCA Championships tennis tournament in Indianapolis on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 16th-seeded American failed to enlarge his comeback winning
streak from three matches, acknowledging the defeat 6-3, 5-7, 6-3
in two hours and 11 minutes.
</P>
<P>
However, Agassi, the former world No. 1 who currently ranked
74th in the world, was far from displeased.
</P>
<P>
"I got more than I expected this week," said the 27-year-old
Agassi, "my desire and competitiveness are still there, they are
what will help me win more matches."
</P>
<P>
Australian Woodforde broke Agassi for 4-2 to take the first
before Agassi battled in the swirling conditions to level the set
at one each.
</P>
<P>
In the final set, Agassi was broken twice, the second time
after saving a match point.
</P>
<P>
Ninth seed Jonas Bjorkman from Sweden needed three sets and
more than two hours to oust American qualifier Tommy Ho. 
</P>
