<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Petr Korda survived big
scares to advance to the semifinals of the Pilot Pen International
tennis tournament in New Haven, Connecticut on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fifth-seeded Czech fended off three break points and four
match points to beat David Wheaton of the United States 4-6, 7-6
(9-7), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
