<HEADLINE> Fernandez Enters Semifinals in Toronto Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Mary Joe Fernandez of the United
States defeated Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria to book the first
semifinal spot at the du Maurier Open in Toronto on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Against a windy and rainy weather, the 10th-seeded Fernandez
overcame 37 unforced errors and seven double-faults to win her
quarterfinal 6-2, 6-7, 6-4 in two hours and 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Fernandez will face either Germany's Anke Huber,
seeded eighth, or third seed Amanda Coetzer of South Africa in
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Conchita Martinez of Spain and Lindsay Davenport of the United
States had their quarterfinal matches interrupted by heavy rain
midway through the second set.
</P>
<P>
Davenport dropped the opening set 4-6 and led 5-4 in the
second. 
</P>
</TEXT>
