<HEADLINE> Brazilian Rivaldo Sets Transfer Record in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian midfielder Rivaldo
became the most expensive transfer in Spain on Friday when he
joined Barcelona for 4 billion pesetas (25 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo, who early served for Spanish club Deportivo La Coruna,
may make his debut for Barcelona on Saturday when the side faces
Sampdoria of Italy.
</P>
<P>
The five-year contract was signed after four hours of talks
with club vice president Joan Gaspart, including a 15 billion
pesetas (95 million US dollars) escape clause.
</P>
<P>
The early record of transfer fee was 19.8 million US dollars
paid by Atletico Madrid for Brazilian striker Juninho this
summer. 
</P>
