<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Stops Illegal Asian Immigrants off Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- the United States would not
allow illegal Asian immigrants on board a vessel to enter the
country, the State Department said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman James Rubin was referring to a vessel Lapas Number 3,
which was intercepted last Tuesday by the Coast Guard.
</P>
<P>
U.S. policy was to prevent illegal immigrants coming to the
country and Washington wanted to make clear to "alien smugglers"
that they "would be wise not to try to send their illegal cargo,"
Rubin said at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
The vessel was intercepted by a crew from the Coast Guard after
it was spotted by aircraft, and was boarded on Wednesday by four
officers of the U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS).
</P>
<P>
INS and Coast Guard officials said the passengers were
undocumented Asian migrants. The ship reportedly was flying a
Mexican flag but its registry was not clear. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
